---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About Gary Tate — Consultates" description="Engineer. Commercial leader. AI practitioner. 35 years across military electronics, enterprise sales, and production AI — now helping leaders make sense of it.">

  <!-- Section 1 — Hero (dark, photo background placeholder) -->
  <section class="about-hero bg-dots-dark">
    <!-- TODO: Replace placeholder with actual hero photo -->
    <!-- <img src="/images/about-hero.webp" alt="" class="about-hero__bg" /> -->
    <div class="about-hero__content">
        <h1 class="text-hero" style="color: #FFFFFF;">Engineer. Commercial leader.<br/>AI practitioner.</h1>
        <p class="text-body-lg" style="color: var(--hero-muted); max-width: 580px;">35 years across military electronics, Silicon Valley coding, enterprise sales leadership, and production AI.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2 — How We Work + Personal Message (combined, photo right) -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="founder-section">
          <div class="founder-section__text">
            <h2 class="founder-heading">How we work</h2>
            <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground mb-10">We run a family consultancy and scale through established partners. Together we bring care and a personal touch to every engagement. You get one accountable team from start to finish.</p>

            <h2 class="founder-heading">A personal message from our founder</h2>
            <div class="founder-letter">
              <p>You don't need to start from scratch. The hard-won skills and experience you already have translate perfectly to working with AI, and I can show you how to apply them effectively.</p>
              <p>I'm Gary C., and if you're here, you're exploring how AI fits into your business.</p>
              <p>I've been where you are. Using AI in my own businesses has saved us time and money and helped us grow, and I learned through continuous learning and trial and error what works and what to avoid. That hard-won experience means you get there faster, with fewer wrong turns.</p>
              <p>I wrote my first code at age 10 in the 80s on a computer I built with my dad. Back then there were no mobile phones, no Internet, and just a handful of TV channels. Since then I've witnessed every major paradigm shift: personal computers, the Internet, social media. AI is on another level, its arrival is unlike anything before, and a shift none of us can afford to ignore. Each shift taught me that early adopters who move with intentionality consistently outperform those who wait. AI follows the same pattern, just faster.</p>
              <p>I've lived and worked in sixteen countries across five continents, and that breadth of experience makes me better at meeting people where they are. I've sat across the table from every kind of leader, in every kind of business, and my goal is always the same: make AI practical and approachable, so you gain clear choices and the confidence to move forward.</p>
              <p>Let's put AI to work for you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="founder-section__photo">
            <img
              src="/images/Me-for-Website-450x600.webp"
              alt="Gary Tate"
              width="450"
              height="600"
              class="founder-section__img"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3 — The Story (editorial timeline) -->
  <section class="bg-secondary" style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 class="text-section mb-12">The through-line</h2>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">1980s</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">I started coding at 10.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">1990s</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Royal Air Force — a decade in military electronics, telecoms, cryptography, and secure communications. Physical systems where mistakes aren't theoretical. Started my own company after leaving in 1997.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">2000s</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Silicon Valley. 8 years as a member of technical staff coding at Juniper Networks. Then Systems Engineering Director at Cyan.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">2010s</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Moved to Asia and transitioned into sales — not because I stopped being technical, but because I could sit in front of a CEO, CTO or CISO and explain the technology in terms that closed deals. MD Sales, VP Sales (three times), CRO — building entire sales organisations from zero. Always deep-tech companies: networking infrastructure, enterprise SaaS, cybersecurity, AI.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">2020s</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">AI wasn't new to me. I'd been selling it at Wedge Networks and Cylance for years. But when ChatGPT launched, I knew from the start that this was something different. That's when I made the decision to focus all of my energies on generative AI.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era">Today</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Today I run AI advisories, I train leaders, I build AI applications, and I serve as a fractional AI executive.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline__entry" data-reveal>
          <span class="timeline__era timeline__era--wide">Why it matters</span>
          <span class="timeline__dot"></span>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Most AI consultants are one thing: technical people who can't explain it to a boardroom, or business people who've never built anything, or trainers teaching from slides they didn't write. I've closed enterprise deals, I train executive cohorts from my own material, and I build production-ready AI applications. That's why the consulting, the training, and the leadership all carry weight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     Hero — dark with placeholder for background photo
     ============================================================ */
  .about-hero {
    background: var(--hero-bg, #0D1117);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem) var(--content-px);
  }

  /* Radial purple glow — matching homepage hero */
  .about-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 40%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    width: 800px;
    height: 500px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(92,59,156,0.25) 0%, rgba(92,59,156,0.10) 40%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  /* Placeholder background image — uncomment and use when photo is ready */
  .about-hero__bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    opacity: 0.4;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .about-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    max-width: var(--content-max, 1140px);
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* ============================================================
     Timeline — CSS Grid, no absolute positioning
     ============================================================ */
  .timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Vertical line */
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 72px;
    top: 12px;
    bottom: 12px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .timeline__entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px 24px 1fr;
    gap: 0 1rem;
    align-items: start;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .timeline__entry:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline__era {
    font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    text-align: right;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-top: 1px;
  }

  .timeline__era--wide {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
  }

  .timeline__dot {
    display: block;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    background: var(--secondary);
    margin-top: 6px;
    justify-self: center;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .timeline::before {
      left: 52px;
    }

    .timeline__entry {
      grid-template-columns: 40px 24px 1fr;
    }

    .timeline__era {
      font-size: 0.65rem;
    }

    .timeline__era--wide {
      font-size: 0.6rem;
    }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     Founder Section — text left, photo right (50/50)
     ============================================================ */
  .founder-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .founder-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--foreground);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .founder-section__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }

  .founder-letter {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    color: var(--secondary-foreground);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .founder-letter p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .founder-letter p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Mobile — stack photo above text */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .founder-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .founder-section__photo {
      order: -1;
    }

    .founder-section__img {
      position: static;
    }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     Timeline scroll reveal — opacity only, no translateY
     ============================================================ */
  .timeline__entry[data-reveal] {
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.6s var(--ease-out);
  }

  .timeline__entry[data-reveal].is-visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .timeline__entry[data-reveal] {
      opacity: 1;
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Wait one frame so the browser paints opacity:0 first,
  // then start observing. Stagger entries that are already
  // in view so they don't all appear at the same instant.
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    const entries = document.querySelectorAll('.timeline__entry[data-reveal]');
    if (!entries.length) return;

    let staggerIndex = 0;

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (items) => {
        items.forEach((item) => {
          if (item.isIntersecting) {
            const el = item.target as HTMLElement;
            const delay = staggerIndex * 200;
            staggerIndex++;
            setTimeout(() => el.classList.add('is-visible'), delay);
            observer.unobserve(el);
          }
        });
      },
      { threshold: 0.2 }
    );

    entries.forEach((entry) => observer.observe(entry));
  });
</script>
